# Laravel Patterns — MyOccasions

## Repository

```php
// app/Repositories/Food/Interface/FoodRepositoryInterface.php
interface FoodRepositoryInterface {
    public function query(array $filters = []): Builder;
    public function findById(int $id): Food;
}

// app/Repositories/Food/Implementation/FoodRepository.php
class FoodRepository implements FoodRepositoryInterface {
    private const DEFAULT_WITH = ['mainKey', 'orderStatusAble.status', 'media'];

    public function query(array $filters = []): Builder {
        return Food::with(self::DEFAULT_WITH)->when(/* filters */);
    }
}
```

- Eloquent queries ONLY in Repository
- Define `DEFAULT_WITH` constant — match what Resource needs
- Return `Builder` for lists; Service handles pagination

## Service

```php
class FoodService implements FoodServiceInterface {
    public function __construct(private FoodRepositoryInterface $repo) {}

    public function list(array $filters): LengthAwarePaginator {
        $perPage = max(1, min(100, (int) ($filters['per_page'] ?? 10)));
        return $this->repo->query($filters)->paginate($perPage);
    }
}
```

- DB transactions in Service, not Controller
- Never duplicate logic — extract shared methods/traits
- Depend on interfaces, not concrete classes

## N+1 Prevention

```php
// ✅ Repository eager loads
Food::with(['mainKey', 'orderStatusAble.status', 'media']);

// ✅ Service adds dynamic relations
$model->loadMissing(['userPermissions', 'role.permissions']);

// ❌ Never access unloaded relations in Resource loops
```

## SOLID

- **S**: One responsibility per class
- **O**: Extend via new implementations, not modifying existing controllers
- **L**: Implementations honor interface contracts
- **I**: Small entity-focused interfaces
- **D**: Inject interfaces; bind in AppServiceProvider
